<subSubSection id="07AF96B5FFC3FFEDF52462C7FDE1CB61" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4F0AC53EFFC3FFEDF52462C7FF00CDA0" blockId="39.[111,649,723,1066]" box="[113,203,723,749]" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">REMARK</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F0AC53EFFC3FFEDF52462E6FDE1CB61" blockId="39.[111,649,723,1066]" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">
The type, 
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFC3FFEDF5BD62E1FD8FCC46" box="[232,580,755,781]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">Service Forestier (Capuron) 3009</emphasis>
, is in bud; the second collection cited by Kostermans has young fruits. Kostermans compared this species with 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFC3FFEDF5FC6346FEC6CC20" box="[169,269,849,876]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFC3FFEDF5FC6346FEC6CC20" box="[169,269,849,876]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">O. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs in the clearly alternate leaves, and with 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFC3FFEDF4C36366FDD1CCC0" box="[406,538,881,908]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="faucherei">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFC3FFEDF4C36366FDD1CCC0" box="[406,538,881,908]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">O. faucherei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a poorly known species with the filaments of the inner three stamens fused. Because the type is in buds, it is not possible to verify if 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFC3FFEDF46863C5FE18CCA1" box="[317,467,976,1003]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrorhiza">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFC3FFEDF46863C5FE18CCA1" box="[317,467,976,1003]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">O. macrorhiza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has free or fused filaments of the inner stamens. I doubt also that the paratype is conspecific with the type.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
